description:
The many cultures represented in New Orleans, combined with the city’s trade routes along the Mississippi River and into the Atlantic Ocean, made New Orleans unlike any other city on earth. In this environment comes a musical genius who hears the many influences and forges Jazz out of them. Phil Schaap tells you about this man: Buddy Bolden.

Find out more in this video series with WKCR personality and Jazz at Lincoln Center curator Phil Schaap!

Visit http://academy.jalc.org to learn more

Phil Schaap - Lecturer
Eric Suquet - Director
Bill Thomas - Director of Photography
Aaron Chandler - Audio Engineer
Richard Emery - Production Assistant
Seton Hawkins - Producer

Theme music composed and performed by Eli Yamin

Recorded September 10, 2013
